  "prompt": "Why maths is importance than other subject?",
  "response": "Mathematics is important, but it's not necessarily more important than other subjects. Each subject has its own unique value and significance. However, mathematics is crucial for several reasons:\n\n1. Problem-solving skills\n- Develops logical thinking\n- Enhances critical reasoning\n- Teaches systematic approach to challenges\n\n2. Practical applications\n- Essential in science and technology\n- Used in engineering, finance, and economics\n- Fundamental in computer programming\n\n3. Cognitive development\n- Improves analytical skills\n- Enhances brain's logical reasoning\n- Develops abstract thinking\n\n4. Career opportunities\n- Wide range of career paths\n- High-demand in STEM fields\n- Better job prospects in technical industries\n\n5. Real-world relevance\n- Helps in daily calculations\n- Useful in budgeting\n- Understanding statistics and data\n\n6. Universal language\n- Consistent across cultures\n- Scientific communication\n- Precise and unambiguous\n\n7. Foundation for other subjects\n- Supports physics, chemistry\n- Crucial in computer science\n- Important in economics\n\nWhile mathematics is extremely important, other subjects like languages, humanities, and sciences are equally valuable for holistic education and personal development. Each subject contributes uniquely to understanding the world and developing skills.",
